                  <handDesc>
                  <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                  <seg type="rubrication">
                  <foreign xml:lang="gez">ኢግዚአብሔር፡</foreign>
                  </seg>
                  <desc>The word for God is not rubricated in the first three works</desc>
                  <desc>Nowhere is there use of columetric layout of rubricated text</desc>
                  </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d1"><locus target="#139r" facs="139"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/> with two guardian angels</desc></decoNote>
                    <decoNote type="miniature" xml:id="d2"><locus target="#140r" facs="140"/><desc><ref type="authFile" corresp="AT1031VirginAndChild"/> with two guardian angels, by another artist</desc></decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                  <list>
                    <item xml:id="e1">
                    <locus target="#1v" facs="002"/>
                    <desc>
                    illegible text, written in pencil
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e2">
                    <locus target="#2v" facs="003"/>
                    <desc>
                    The front foreguard sheet (two folios) appears to be taken from another, much older book.  On every page there are faint remains of the text which was originally on the sheet.  The text on 2v seems clear enough to suggest a hand of the 16th century
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a1">
                    <locus target="#3r" facs="003"/>
                    <desc>
                    <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur"/> begin with the traditional heading, but with the addition of <foreign xml:lang="gez">አርአያ</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e3">
                    <desc>
                    There are marginal notations from the strophe counting system, with the number 10 appearing at regular intervals
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e4">
                    <locus target="#61r" facs="061"/>
                    <desc>
                    The midpoint of the Psalms is marked with a small ornamental cross in the margin
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a2">
                    <desc>
                    The spiritual meanings of the Hebrew letters in Psalm 118 is from the new, common system
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e5">
                    <desc>
                      <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Chp151"/> contains all four of the plusses that make up the long edition
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e6">
                    <desc>
                    <title type="complete" ref="LIT2000Mazmur"/> end with the five-line poem that begins, “the Psalms of David are like a garden.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="e7">
                    <desc>
                    The fourth biblical canticle is “Prayer of Hana, mother of Samuel, prophetess.”
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a3">
                    <locus target="#138r" facs="138"/>
                    <desc type="ScribalNoteCommencing">
                    at the conclusion of the <title type="complete" ref="LIT2362Songof"/>, there is a scribal notation of the timeframe of copying the book: This Psalter was started on Thursday, the 17th of Näḥase, and was completed on the 2nd of Pagwamen
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                    <item xml:id="a4">
                    <locus target="#141r" facs="141"/>
                    <desc type="OwnershipNote">
                    Note of secondary ownership: <foreign xml:lang="gez">ቀሺ ወልደ ማርያም</foreign>
                    </desc>
                    </item>
                  </list>
                </additions>
